Jobs continues his efforts to streamline accounting at Apple.
Surprisingly, how costs were recorded – usually starting with “standard costs” that were quantified to mere guesswork and then adjusted with “deviation” – he developed an automated factory that ensured that business costs could be determined to the smallest extent.
How the Pope was enthralled:
Jobs tells the story of the "Blue Box" he built with Steve Wozniak, a device with which one could sneak into the phone company and have long-distance conversations for free.
