"It had a remarkable impact on me, it was the only company I had seen at the age and it shaped my views on what a company was and how well it treated its employees."
Later, Jobs became one of HP’s employees visiting the company’s research labs in Palo Alto, where he saw “the first desktop computer ever made.”
He was as big as a suitcase, had a small screen with brown tube and I fell in love with him.
I would climb up at HP as a teenager and hang on this machine and write programs for her.
How to improve innovations:
