Scott Peterson’s slipper is famous for using the form of the past when he claimed his dead wife was still alive and triggered a national search for her.
Deceiving people can also use a distancing language: “I had no sexual relationship with this woman...Miss Lewinsky” or if you repeat a tricky question altogether.
The most common verbal signs are subtle.
Some people use "qualifying language" when answering a tricky question: "Well... to tell you the truth... as far as I know... to the best of my knowledge and conscience."
