The conversion of analogues to digital signals has been one of the most important changes in the world in recent years.
The Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) rejected the constitutional lawsuits filed by the Senate and the House of Representatives against the presidential decree, and by which the transition from analogue to digital signals from 2021 to 2015 must be pre-determined, due to the lack of eight votes required to challenge the law.
