Replacing analog signals with digital is one of the most important changes that has taken place in recent years around the world, and it results in better use of the radio spectrum, increased signal quality and more channels.
The postponement of the transition, she said, is a postponement of the benefits of digitization, which is a decision in the public interest, which has not only technical aspects, "because it encompasses economic, social, political and security aspects."
These matters, she stressed, "made the action of the whole system necessary, according to the principle of economic management by the state, they contained a group of features that placed the constitution in the hands of the central government."
She recalled that many countries around the world had already implemented the digital transformation, through the government, even though they had highly specialized facilities.
It cannot be concluded that the government would interfere with the powers of Congress with the issue of the contested legislative decree, because the laws passed by the legislature would be respected," she assured.
